Noxious Foe
tasks.description:
Noxious Foe is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill an aberrant spectre. Killing deviant spectres in the Catacombs of Kourend do not count towards this task.
This achievement requires 60 Slayer to complete. Boosts can be used.

tasks.name: Barrows Novice
tasks.description:
Barrows Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to open the Barrows chest 10 times.
Completion of the quest Priest in Peril is required to complete this task, as this quest is required to enter Morytania.

tasks.name: Defence? What Defence?
tasks.description:
Defence? What Defence? is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill any Barrows brother using only magic damage.
Completion of the quest Priest in Peril is required to complete this task, as this quest is required to enter Morytania.

tasks.name: Big, Black and Fiery
tasks.description: Big, Black and Fiery is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a black dragon. While the King Black Dragon and brutal black dragons count towards this task, baby black dragons do not.

tasks.name: The Demonic Punching Bag
tasks.description:
The Demonic Punching Bag is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a bloodveld or Mutated Bloodveld.
A Slayer level of 50 is required to damage bloodvelds. Boosts can be used.

tasks.name: Preparation Is Key
tasks.description: Preparation Is Key is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta without suffering any poison damage.

tasks.name: Fighting as Intended II
tasks.description: Fighting as Intended II is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta on a free to play world.

tasks.name: Bryophyta Novice
tasks.description: Bryophyta Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta and loot her chest with a mossy key once. The regular strategies can be followed to complete this task.

tasks.name: Protection from Moss
tasks.description:
This article contains Combat Achievements that can be completed on free-to-play worlds.
Players without membership cannot claim any rewards or fully complete any tier of the achievements.

tasks.name: A Slow Death
tasks.description: A Slow Death is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta with either poison or venom being the final source of damage.

tasks.name: Deranged Archaeologist Novice
tasks.description: Deranged Archaeologist Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist 10 times.

tasks.name: The Walking Volcano
tasks.description: The Walking Volcano is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a fire giant.

tasks.name: Giant Mole Novice
tasks.description: Giant Mole Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole 10 times.

tasks.name: Not So Great After All
tasks.description: Not So Great After All is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to finish off a greater demon with a demonbane weapon.

tasks.name: A Greater Foe
tasks.description:
A Greater Foe is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a greater demon.
Killing a greater demon in the Wilderness Slayer Cave does not count for this achievement.

tasks.name: A Demon's Best Friend
tasks.description: A Demon's Best Friend is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a hellhound. Killing Cerberus counts for this achievement.

tasks.name: King Black Dragon Novice
tasks.description: King Black Dragon Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 10 times.

tasks.name: Shayzien Protector
tasks.description: Shayzien Protector is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a lizardman shaman in Molch which has not dealt damage to anyone, excluding the damage that its spawns deal.

tasks.name: A Scaley Encounter
tasks.description: A Scaley Encounter is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Lizardman Shaman.

tasks.name: Into the Den of Giants
tasks.description: Into the Den of Giants is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a hill giant, moss giant, and a fire giant in the Giants' Den within the Shayzien region.

tasks.name: Fighting as Intended
tasks.description: Fighting as Intended is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor on a free to play world.

tasks.name: Sleeping Giant
tasks.description: Sleeping Giant is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor whilst he is immobilized.

tasks.name: Obor Novice
tasks.description: Obor Novice is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill Obor once and then loot his chest.

tasks.name: Sarachnis Novice
tasks.description: Sarachnis Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis 10 times.

tasks.name: Scurrius Novice
tasks.description: Scurrius Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Scurrius once.

tasks.name: Sit Rat
tasks.description: Sit Rat is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius with a ratbane weapon in a private instance.

tasks.name: Calm Before the Storm
tasks.description: Calm Before the Storm is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to repair either a mast or a totem pole.

tasks.name: Master of Buckets
tasks.description: Master of Buckets is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to extinguish at least 5 fires during a single Tempoross fight.

tasks.name: Tempoross Novice
tasks.description: Tempoross Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross 5 times.

tasks.name: Fire in the Hole!
tasks.description: Fire in the Hole! is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to attack Tempoross from both sides by loading both cannons on both ships.

tasks.name: Mummy!
tasks.description: Mummy! is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to heal a pyromancer with a rejuvenation potion after they have fallen.

tasks.name: Handyman
tasks.description: Handyman is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to repair a brazier which has been destroyed by the Wintertodt.

tasks.name: Cosy
tasks.description: Cosy is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt with four pieces of warm equipment equipped.

tasks.name: Wintertodt Novice
tasks.description: Wintertodt Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt 5 times.

tasks.name: A Slithery Encounter
tasks.description: A Slithery Encounter is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a wyrm. Killing a wyrmling will not count for this combat achievement.

tasks.name: Elemental Company
tasks.description: Elemental Company is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without attacking the ice or fire elemental.

tasks.name: Let them fight
tasks.description: Let them fight is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans while having them kill at least 10 ice or fire elementals.

tasks.name: One by one
tasks.description: One by one is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill one of the Royal Titans at a time, without attacking the other.

tasks.name: Barrows Champion
tasks.description: Barrows Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Barrows chest 25 times.

tasks.name: Can't Touch Me
tasks.description:
Can't Touch Me is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dharok, Verac, Torag, and Guthan without letting them attack the player with melee.
If you have killed 0 of the brothers and get hit by the first brother you try to kill, leaving and re-entering the crypt will NOT reset the task, so you will need to open the chest and start over.
After killing the 4 brothers without being hit, the combat achievement will not unlock until after opening the chest.

tasks.name: Pray for Success
tasks.description: Pray for Success is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill all six Barrows Brothers and loot the Barrows chest without taking any damage from any of the brothers.

tasks.name: Brutal, Big, Black and Firey
tasks.description: Brutal, Big, Black and Firey is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a brutal black dragon. A Slayer level of 77 is required to damage a brutal black dragon.

tasks.name: Quick Cutter
tasks.description: Quick Cutter is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill all 3 of Bryophyta's growthlings within 3 seconds of the first one dying.

tasks.name: Bryophyta Champion
tasks.description: Bryophyta Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta and loot her chest with a mossy key 5 times.

tasks.name: Chaos Fanatic Champion
tasks.description: Chaos Fanatic Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic 10 times.

tasks.name: Sorry, What Was That?
tasks.description: Sorry, What Was That? is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic without anyone being hit by his explosion attack.

tasks.name: Mage of the Ruins
tasks.description:
Mage of the Ruins is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist with only magical attacks.
Damage inflicted by a ring of recoil or by the special attack of a dragonfire shield also counts as magical for the purpose of this task.

tasks.name: Crazy Archaeologist Champion
tasks.description: Crazy Archaeologist Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist 10 times.

tasks.name: I'd Rather Not Learn
tasks.description: I'd Rather Not Learn is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist without anyone being hit by his "Rain of Knowledge" attack.

tasks.name: Dagannoth Prime Champion
tasks.description: Dagannoth Prime Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime 10 times.

tasks.name: Dagannoth Rex Champion
tasks.description: Dagannoth Rex Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex 10 times.

tasks.name: A Frozen King
tasks.description: A Frozen King is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex whilst he is immobilized. Curse spells, grasp spells, and ice spells count towards this achievement.

tasks.name: Dagannoth Supreme Champion
tasks.description: Dagannoth Supreme Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Supreme 10 times.

tasks.name: I'd Rather Be Illiterate
tasks.description: I'd Rather Be Illiterate is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist without anyone being hit by his "Learn to Read" attack.

tasks.name: Deranged Archaeologist Champion
tasks.description: Deranged Archaeologist Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist 25 times.

tasks.name: Mage of the Swamp
tasks.description:
Mage of the Swamp is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist with only magical attacks.
Damage inflicted by a ring of recoil or by the special attack of a dragonfire shield also counts as magical for the purpose of this task.

tasks.name: A Smashing Time
tasks.description: A Smashing Time is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a gargoyle, requiring 75 Slayer in order to be harmed.

tasks.name: Giant Mole Champion
tasks.description: Giant Mole Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant mole 25 times.

tasks.name: Avoiding Those Little Arms
tasks.description: Avoiding Those Little Arms is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole without anyone taking damage from her.

tasks.name: King Black Dragon Champion
tasks.description: King Black Dragon Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 25 times.

tasks.name: Hide Penetration
tasks.description: Hide Penetration is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the King Black Dragon with a weapon using the stab attack style.

tasks.name: Antifire Protection
tasks.description: Dragonfire is the fiery breath attack used by most dragons, hence the name. While it can deal considerable damage to unprepared players, the damage may be negated with certain shields, (super) antifire potions and Protect from Magic.

tasks.name: Claw Clipper
tasks.description: Claw Clipper is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon with the Protect from Melee prayer activated. This combat achievement will only be completed if Protect from Melee is the only activated prayer, so turn off all other prayers before finishing the kill.

tasks.name: Master of Broad Weaponry
tasks.description:
Master of Broad Weaponry is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a kurask.
Killing a kurask requires level 70 Slayer. Players must also have leaf-bladed weaponry to kill it. This includes broad ammunition and the Magic Dart spell (requiring a Slayer's staff).
Note: The kurask in the southern cave of the Fremennik Slayer Dungeon can only be harmed while on a kurask Slayer task.

tasks.name: Lunar Triplet
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Lunar Triplet is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest after defeating all three Moons in the Moons of Peril.

tasks.name: Back to Our Roots
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Back to Our Roots is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril with a dragon scimitar without leaving Neypotzli.

tasks.name: Moons of Peril Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description:
Moons of Peril Speed-Trialist is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril in one run in under 8 minutes.
The timer begins upon entering the first boss room (the area where players use the statue to enter the boss arena). Importantly, this means supplies collection before fighting the first Moon does not count towards the timer.

tasks.name: Perilous Novice
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Perilous Novice is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest 5 times.

tasks.name: Sit Back and Relax
tasks.description: Sit Back and Relax is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to deal 100 damage to creatures using undead thralls. This can be accomplished accumulatively across multiple undead thrall casts and multiple enemies.

tasks.name: Obor Champion
tasks.description: Obor Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor and open his chest 5 times.

tasks.name: Squashing the Giant
tasks.description: Squashing the Giant is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor without taking any damage off prayer.

tasks.name: Back to the Wall
tasks.description: Back to the Wall is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor without being pushed back more than one square by his knockback attack.

tasks.name: Newspaper Enthusiast
tasks.description: Newspaper Enthusiast is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis with a crush weapon.

tasks.name: Sarachnis Champion
tasks.description: Sarachnis Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis 25 times.

tasks.name: Efficient Pest Control
tasks.description: Efficient Pest Control is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill six giant rats in Scurrius' lair in 3 seconds.

tasks.name: Scurrius Champion
tasks.description: Scurrius Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius 10 times.

tasks.name: Perfect Scurrius
tasks.description: Perfect Scurrius is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius in a private instance without taking damage from his Tail Swipe and Falling Bricks attacks, whilst praying correctly against his ranged and magic attacks.

tasks.name: A Frozen Foe from the Past
tasks.wikiTitle: A Frozen Foe from the Past
tasks.description: A Frozen Foe from the Past is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a skeletal wyvern.

tasks.name: Demonbane Weaponry
tasks.description:
Demonbane Weaponry is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo with a demonbane weapon equipped.
Holy water does not count as a demonbane weapon for the purpose of this achievement.

tasks.name: Demonic Weakening
tasks.description: Demonic Weakening is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill Skotizo with no altars active.

tasks.name: Skotizo Champion
tasks.description: Skotizo Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo once.

tasks.name: Tempoross Champion
tasks.description: Tempoross Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross 10 times.

tasks.name: The Lone Angler
tasks.description: The Lone Angler is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross alone without getting hit by any fires, torrents or waves.

tasks.name: Hueycoatl Champion
tasks.description: Hueycoatl Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl once.

tasks.name: You're a wizard
tasks.description:
You're a wizard is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl using only earth spells. Only the player seeking the achievement must use earth spells; other players fighting the boss can use any gear.

Note that rings of recoil will fail this task; all damage must be done via earth spells.

tasks.name: Leaving No One Behind
tasks.description: Leaving No One Behind is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt without any of the pyromancers falling. It is only completed if at least 500 points are earned in the fight. This task can often be achieved passively by playing Wintertodt in the official Wintertodt worlds.

tasks.name: Can We Fix It?
tasks.description: Can We Fix It? is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt without allowing all 4 braziers to be broken at the same time.

tasks.name: Wintertodt Champion
tasks.description: Wintertodt Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt 10 times.

tasks.name: Royal Titan Champion
tasks.description: Royal Titan Champion is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 10 times.

tasks.name: Royal Titan Adept
tasks.description: Royal Titan Adept is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 25 times.

tasks.name: It takes too long
tasks.description: It takes too long is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill both the Royal Titans while they are charging up their area attack. Both titans must die during the same charging phase.

tasks.description: Abyssal Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire 20 times.

tasks.name: Don't Whip Me
tasks.description:
Don't Whip Me is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire without being hit by any external tentacles.
This achievement is easily obtained by only attacking the vents after having successfully disoriented the Abyssal Sire with a shadow spell, preferably Shadow Barrage as it is 100% effective. Once the Abyssal Sire roots itself after having reached 200 HP, the player should only stay in the three centremost rows of squares to avoid any damage from the tentacles.

tasks.name: They Grow Up Too Fast
tasks.description: They Grow Up Too Fast is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Abyssal Sire before any spawns mature into a scion.

tasks.name: The Flincher
tasks.description:
The Flincher is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental without taking any damage from its attacks.
If any player takes damage from its attacks, everyone involved in the kill will fail.

tasks.name: Hoarder
tasks.description:
Hoarder is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental without it unequipping any of their items.
Much like The Flincher, if any player has their equipment unequipped, everyone involved in the kill will fail.

tasks.name: Praying to the Gods
tasks.description:
Praying to the Gods is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic 10 times, without drinking any potion which restores prayer, or leaving the Wilderness. 
Warning: Entering Ferox Enclave will reset the kill count for this combat task. Even though it is technically in the Wilderness, it is not considered wilderness for the purpose of this task. In general, only places where you risk losing items count.

tasks.description: Heal No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians without letting Dawn receive any healing from her orbs.

tasks.name: Hespori Adept
tasks.description: Hespori Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori 5 times.

tasks.name: Hesporisn't
tasks.description:
Hesporisn't is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off the Hespori with a special attack.
Enchanted bolt special effects can trigger this achievement if the bolt effect activates on the last hit, such as Diamond bolts (e). Emerald bolts (e) have the highest chance of activation, making them also effective for this.

tasks.name: Weed Whacker
tasks.description: Weed Whacker is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill all of the Hespori's flowers within 5 seconds.

tasks.name: Demonbane Weaponry II
tasks.description: Demonbane Weaponry II is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off K'ril Tsutsaroth with a demonbane weapon.

tasks.name: K'ril Tsutsaroth Adept
tasks.description: K'ril Tsutsaroth Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth 50 times.

tasks.name: Yarr No More
tasks.description: Yarr No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for K'ril Tsutsaroth without him using his special attack.

tasks.name: Demonic Showdown
tasks.description: Demonic Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off K'ril Tsutsaroth whilst all of his bodyguards are dead.

tasks.name: Kalphite Queen Adept
tasks.description: Kalphite Queen Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen 25 times.

tasks.name: Chitin Penetrator
tasks.description: Chitin Penetrator is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen while her defence was last lowered by the player.

tasks.name: Who Is the King Now?
tasks.description: Who Is the King Now? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 10 times in a private instance without leaving.

tasks.name: Unnecessary Optimisation
tasks.description:
Unnecessary Optimisation is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken after killing all four tentacles.
The Enormous Tentacles can be killed before waking the Kraken.

tasks.name: Krakan't Hurt Me
tasks.description: Krakan't Hurt Me is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 25 times in a private instance without leaving or logging out.

tasks.name: Kraken Adept
tasks.description: Kraken Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 20 times.

tasks.name: Airborne Showdown
tasks.description: Airborne Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off Kree'arra whilst all of his bodyguards are dead.

tasks.name: Kree'arra Adept
tasks.description: Kree'arra Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra 50 times.

tasks.name: Betrayal
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Betrayal is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon using the associated weapon.

tasks.name: Fortified
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Fortified is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon without consuming any supplies.

tasks.name: Moons of Peril Speed-Chaser
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description:
Moons of Peril Speed-Chaser is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril in one run in under 6 minutes.
The timer begins upon entering the first boss room (the area where players use the statue to enter the boss arena). Importantly, this means supplies collection before fighting the first Moon does not count towards the timer.

tasks.name: The Clone Zone
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: The Clone Zone is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Eclipse Moon without attacking her outside of her clone attack.

tasks.name: Perilous Dancer
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Perilous Dancer is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all the Moons of Peril in one run, while only taking damage from regular attacks.

tasks.name: Fat of the Land
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Fat of the Land is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat 30 Moons of Peril without leaving Neypotzli.

tasks.name: Perilous Champion
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description:
Perilous Champion is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest 25 times in the Moons of Peril.

If you are solely farming the combat achievement, defeating Eclipse Moon is a quick method of completing it. After defeating Eclipse Moon, you will be teleported into the Blue Moon area with the salamander sites. Run past the salamander sites to the far south-east entrance. Then continue running past the Blood Moon chamber entrance and take a sip of tea from the cooking stove on the way to...

tasks.name: Phantom Muspah Adept
tasks.prereqs: Secrets of the North quest; 69 Agility; 64 Thieving; 56 Hunter
tasks.description: Phantom Muspah Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah at least once.

tasks.name: Ready to Pounce
tasks.description: Ready to Pounce is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis without her using her range attack twice in a row.

tasks.name: Inspect Repellent
tasks.description: Inspect Repellent is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis without her dealing damage to anyone.

tasks.name: I Can't Reach That
tasks.description: I Can't Reach That is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia without taking any damage from her.

tasks.name: Scorpia Adept
tasks.description: Scorpia Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia 10 times.

tasks.name: Guardians No More
tasks.description: Guardians No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia without killing her guardians.

tasks.name: Skotizo Adept
tasks.description: Skotizo Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo 5 times.

tasks.name: Why Cook?
tasks.description: Why Cook? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross, getting rewarded with 10 reward permits from a single Tempoross fight.

tasks.name: Dress Like You Mean It
tasks.description:
Dress Like You Mean It is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross while wearing all four pieces of the angler's outfit. Players may mix and match regular angler's outfit pieces with spirit angler's outfit pieces.
The outfit can either be obtained from the Fishing Trawler (15 Fishing minimum) or aerial fishing (43 Fishing and 35 Hunter). However, 34 Fishing is required in order to wear it.

tasks.name: I'm your son
tasks.description: I'm your son is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl whilst wearing two pieces of Hueycoatl hide armour. Only the player seeking the achievement must do this; other players fighting the boss can use any gear.

tasks.name: Hueycoatl Adept
tasks.description: Hueycoatl Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl 10 times.

tasks.name: Pillar Lover
tasks.description: Pillar Lover is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl whilst it is vulnerable.

tasks.name: Nightmare Adept
tasks.description: Nightmare Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Nightmare once.

tasks.name: Theatre of Blood: SM Adept
tasks.description: Theatre of Blood: SM Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode 1 time.

tasks.name: Confident Raider
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Confident Raider is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 100 or above.

tasks.name: Movin' on up
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Movin' on up is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 50 or above.

tasks.name: Novice Tomb Looter
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Novice Tomb Looter is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut at any level 25 times.

tasks.name: Novice Tomb Explorer
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Novice Tomb Explorer is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at any level once.

tasks.name: Venenatis Adept
tasks.description: Venenatis Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Venenatis 10 times. Both Venenatis and her singles-plus variant Spindel kills count towards this task.

tasks.name: Vet'ion Adept
tasks.description: Vet'ion Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vet'ion 10 times. Both Vet'ion and his singles-plus variant Calvar'ion kills count towards this task.

tasks.name: Why Fletch?
tasks.description: Why Fletch? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt after earning 3000 or more points during the fight.

tasks.name: Zulrah Adept
tasks.description: Zulrah Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah 25 times.

tasks.name: Royal Titan Speed-Runner
tasks.description: Royal Titan Speed-Runner is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans in under 1 minute and 30 seconds.

tasks.name: Perfect Royal Titan
tasks.description: Perfect Royal Titans is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without getting hit by any avoidable damage.

tasks.name: Titan Killer
tasks.description: Titan Killer is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 15 times without anyone leaving the instance. If a player joins the fight, the current streak will be reset to 0. If a player leaves the fight, the task will be failed and a new instance will need to be created.

tasks.name: I need room
tasks.description: I need room is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans while extinguishing all fires and melting all icicles before they dissipate naturally.

Respiratory Runner
tasks.description:
Respiratory Runner is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire after only stunning him once.
This task fails whenever Sire wakes up from a stun; killing the respiratory systems via safespotting or tanking the tentacles must be done before stunning Sire. Likewise, enough damage to the Sire must be dealt or a shadow spell cast to disorient it exactly once.
Leaving the nexus will fail the achievement attempt unless you don't wake up the Sire.

tasks.name: Perfect Sire
tasks.description: Perfect Sire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire without taking damage from the external tentacles, miasma pools, explosion or damage from the Abyssal Sire without praying the appropriate protection prayer.

tasks.name: Demonic Rebound
tasks.description: Demonic Rebound is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to use Vengeance against the Abyssal Sire's explosion attack.

tasks.name: Abyssal Veteran
tasks.description: Abyssal Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire 50 times.

tasks.name: Alchemical Veteran
tasks.description: Alchemical Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 75 times.

tasks.name: Without Ralos' Light
tasks.description: Without Ralos' Light is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl without losing any prayer points.

tasks.name: Amoxliatl Speed-Chaser
tasks.description: Amoxliatl Speed-Chaser is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl in less than 30 seconds. You can do this on a slayer task.

tasks.name: Relaxxor
tasks.description: Relaxxor is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor after destroying six eggs.

tasks.name: Araxxor Veteran
tasks.description: Araxxor Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 25 times.

tasks.name: Araxxor Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Araxxor Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 4 times within 10 minutes.

tasks.name: Reflecting on This Encounter
tasks.prereqs: The Fremennik Exiles quest; 65 Crafting; 60 Slayer; 60 Smithing; 60 Fishing; 55 Runecraft; 60 Mining
tasks.description: Reflecting on This Encounter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a basilisk knight. Basilisk knights are only found in the Jormungand's Prison on the Island of Stone. In order to access the dungeon, the quest Fremennik Exiles must be completed.

tasks.name: Callisto Veteran
tasks.description: Callisto Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Callisto 20 times. Both Callisto and his singles-plus variant Artio kills count towards this task.

tasks.name: Unrequired Antifire
tasks.description: Unrequired Antifire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus without taking any damage from her lava pool attacks.

tasks.name: Ghost Buster
tasks.description: Ghost Buster is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus after successfully negating 6 or more attacks from Summoned Souls.

tasks.name: Cerberus Veteran
tasks.description: Cerberus Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus 75 times.

tasks.name: Anti-Bite Mechanics
tasks.description: Anti-Bite Mechanics is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus without taking any melee damage.

tasks.name: Undying Raid Team
tasks.description: Undying Raid Team is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric raid without anyone dying.

tasks.name: Together We'll Fall
tasks.description: Together We'll Fall is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill all three Vanguards within ten seconds of killing the first one.

tasks.name: Shayzien Specialist
tasks.description: Shayzien Specialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for a lizardman shaman without taking any damage from them.

tasks.name: Redemption Enthusiast
tasks.description: Redemption Enthusiast is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to destroy the Abyssal portal without letting Vespula land.

tasks.name: Perfectly Balanced
tasks.description:
Perfectly Balanced is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Vanguards without them resetting their health.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

tasks.name: Mutta-diet
tasks.description: Mutta-diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the muttadiles without letting them heal from the meat tree.

tasks.name: Kill It with Fire
tasks.description:
Kill It with Fire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish the ice demon off with a fire spell.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

tasks.name: Dancing with Statues
tasks.description:
Dancing with Statues is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill credit for one of the stone guardians without taking damage from their falling rocks attack.
Use a flinch method to reduce the chances of the guardians attacking. The falling rock attack has a 3x3 AoE centered on the tile it would fall on, so run two spaces away to avoid getting hit.
While regular accounts only need to do more than 50% of the damage to receive kill credit, Ironmen accounts need to do 100% of the damage for...

tasks.name: Cryo No More
tasks.description:
Cryo No More is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for the Ice Demon without taking any damage.

Iron players must kill the Ice Demon solo to be eligible.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

tasks.name: Chambers of Xeric Veteran
tasks.description: Chambers of Xeric Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric 25 times.

tasks.name: Blizzard Dodger
tasks.description: Blizzard Dodger is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for the Ice Demon without activating the Protect from Range prayer.

tasks.name: Dust Seeker
tasks.description: Dust Seeker is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a challenge mode Chambers of Xeric run in the targeted time.

tasks.name: Chaos Elemental Veteran
tasks.description: Chaos Elemental Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental 25 times.

tasks.name: Reminisce
tasks.description: Reminisce is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana in a private instance using only melee.

tasks.name: Commander Zilyana Veteran
tasks.description: Commander Zilyana Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana 100 times.

tasks.name: Hot on Your Feet
tasks.description: Hot on Your Feet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast without killing or taking damage from the dark energy core.

tasks.name: Finding the Weak Spot
tasks.description:
Finding the Weak Spot is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish off the Corporeal Beast with a dragon halberd or crystal halberd special attack.
For this task to completed successfully, the halberd has to be using the stab attack style.

tasks.name: Corporeal Beast Veteran
tasks.description: Corporeal Beast Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast 25 times.

tasks.name: Chicken Killer
tasks.description: Chicken Killer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast alone.

tasks.name: Corrupted Gauntlet Veteran
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Corrupted Gauntlet Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Corrupted Gauntlet 5 times.

tasks.name: 3, 2, 1 - Mage
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: The Crystalline Hunllef is the boss monster within the Gauntlet. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Hunllef.

tasks.name: Wolf Puncher
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Wolf Puncher is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without making more than one attuned weapon within The Gauntlet.

tasks.name: Gauntlet Veteran
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Gauntlet Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Gauntlet 5 times. Completions of the Corrupted Gauntlet will also count towards this task.

tasks.name: Egniol Diet
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Egniol Diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without making an egniol potion, within The Gauntlet.

tasks.name: Crystalline Warrior
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Crystalline Warrior is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef with a full set of perfected crystal armour equipped.

tasks.name: 3, 2, 1 - Range
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: The Crystalline Hunllef is the boss monster within the Gauntlet. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Hunllef.

tasks.name: From One King to Another
tasks.description:
From One King to Another is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime using a rune thrownaxe special attack, bounced off Dagannoth Rex. 

Ironmen cannot receive help from other players to help tank the Kings.
For the task to count, the special attack must be the last attack made when Prime's death animation finishes.

tasks.name: Death to the Seer King
tasks.description: Death to the Seer King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime whilst under attack by Dagannoth Supreme and Dagannoth Rex.

tasks.name: Toppling the Diarchy
tasks.description: Toppling the Diarchy is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex and one other Dagannoth king at the exact same time.

tasks.name: Death to the Warrior King
tasks.description: Death to the Warrior King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex whilst under attack by Dagannoth Supreme and Dagannoth Prime.

tasks.name: Rapid Succession
tasks.description: Rapid Succession is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill all three Dagannoth Kings within 9 seconds of the first one. Ironmen cannot use main accounts to help tank the Kings to complete this challenge.

tasks.name: Death to the Archer King
tasks.description: Death to the Archer King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Supreme whilst under attack by Dagannoth Prime and Dagannoth Rex.

tasks.name: If Gorillas Could Fly
tasks.prereqs: Monkey Madness 2 quest; 69 Slayer; 70 Crafting; 60 Hunter; 55 Agility; 55 Thieving; 60 Firemaking
tasks.description: If Gorillas Could Fly is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a demonic gorilla.

tasks.name: Hitting Them Where It Hurts
tasks.prereqs: Monkey Madness 2 quest; 69 Slayer; 70 Crafting; 60 Hunter; 55 Agility; 55 Thieving; 60 Firemaking
tasks.description: Hitting Them Where It Hurts is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish off a demonic gorilla with a demonbane weapon.

tasks.name: Exposed Doom
tasks.prereqs: The Final Dawn quest; 66 Thieving; 52 Runecrafting; 52 Fletching; 55 Mining; 48 Slayer; 46 Agility; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Exposed Doom is an elite combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl during its melee charge phase at any delve level.

tasks.name: Doom Crawler
tasks.prereqs: The Final Dawn quest; 66 Thieving; 52 Runecrafting; 52 Fletching; 55 Mining; 48 Slayer; 46 Agility; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Doom Crawler is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 1 in less than 30 seconds.

tasks.name: Doom Adept
tasks.prereqs: The Final Dawn quest; 66 Thieving; 52 Runecrafting; 52 Fletching; 55 Mining; 48 Slayer; 46 Agility; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 10 Construction
tasks.description: Doom Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 3.

tasks.name: Duke Sucellus Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Duke Sucellus Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus in under 1 minute, without a slayer task.

tasks.name: Duke Sucellus Adept
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Duke Sucellus Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus once after completion of Desert Treasure II.

tasks.name: I was here first!
tasks.description: I was here first! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a jaguar warrior using a claw-type weapon special attack.

tasks.name: Furball
tasks.description: Furball is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete wave 4 of the Fortis Colosseum without taking avoidable damage from a manticore.

tasks.name: Denied
tasks.description: Denied is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete wave 7 without the minotaur ever healing other enemies.

tasks.name: Fragment of Seren Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Fragment of Seren Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement that requires the Fragment of Seren boss fight to be completed in less than four minutes. Completion of Song of the Elves is required to attempt this achievement as the fight during the quest does not count. The fight can be attempted at the Memoriam Device in Prifddinas.

tasks.name: Galvek Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Dragon Slayer 2 quest; 200 Quest Points; 75 Magic; 70 Smithing; 68 Mining; 62 Crafting; 60 Agility; 60 Thieving; 50 Construction; 50 Hitpoints
tasks.description:
Galvek Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Galvek in less than 3 minutes. The fight can be attempted at the Pool of Dreams to the east on the Myths' Guild's ground floor.
The player must deal 1200 damage to Galvek in 300 ticks, or 49 possible Dragon hunter crossbow (Rapid) attacks averaging 24.48 damage per attack.

tasks.name: Ourg Freezer II
tasks.description: Ourg Freezer II is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor without him attacking any players.

tasks.name: General Graardor Veteran
tasks.description: General Graardor Veteran is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill General Graardor 100 times.

tasks.name: Hard Hitter
tasks.description: Hard Hitter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole within four hits that deal damage.

tasks.name: Glough Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Monkey Madness 2 quest; 69 Slayer; 70 Crafting; 60 Hunter; 55 Agility; 55 Thieving; 60 Firemaking
tasks.description: Glough Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Glough in less than 2 minutes and 30 seconds. The fight can be attempted at the burning brazier in Zooknock's house.

tasks.name: Perfect Grotesque Guardians
tasks.description:
Perfect Grotesque Guardians is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians whilst completing the Don't Look at the Eclipse, Prison Break, Granite Footwork, Heal No More, Static Awareness, and Done before Dusk tasks.
This means the player must kill the Grotesque Guardians without doing the following:

Taking damage from Dusk's blinding attack.
Taking damage from Dusk's prison attack.
Taking damage from Dawn's rockfall attack.
Letting Dawn receive any healing from her orbs.
Being...

tasks.name: Grotesque Guardians Veteran
tasks.description: Grotesque Guardians Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 50 times.

tasks.name: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians in 2:00 or less. Despite the official description, a time of exactly 2:00.00 will count for the achievement.

tasks.name: From Dusk...
tasks.description: From Dusk... is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 10 times without leaving the instance.

tasks.name: Done before Dusk
tasks.description: Done before Dusk is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians before Dusk uses his prison attack for a second time.

tasks.name: Plant-Based Diet
tasks.description: Plant-Based Diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori without losing any prayer points.

tasks.name: Hespori Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Hespori Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori in 48 seconds or less.

tasks.name: The Bane of Demons
tasks.description: The Bane of Demons is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat K'ril Tsutsaroth in a private instance using only demonbane spells.

tasks.name: K'ril Tsutsaroth Veteran
tasks.description: K'ril Tsutsaroth Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth 100 times.

tasks.name: Demonic Defence
tasks.description: Demonic Defence is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth in a private instance without taking any of his melee hits.

tasks.name: Prayer Smasher
tasks.description: Prayer Smasher is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen using only Verac's flail as a weapon. Inflicting recoil damage with a ring of recoil, ring of suffering, echo boots, or Vengeance is not allowed. This has to be done solo; damage from another player will invalidate the kill even if they are also using a flail. However, damage from thralls and poison inflicted via the serpentine helm are allowed, and the kill can be completed over several trips.

tasks.name: Kalphite Queen Veteran
tasks.description: Kalphite Queen Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen 50 times.

tasks.name: Insect Deflection
tasks.description:
Insect Deflection is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen by using the Vengeance spell as the finishing blow.
Another account can cast Vengeance Other on the player and it will count toward this combat achievement.

tasks.name: Ten-tacles
tasks.description: Ten-tacles is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 50 times in a private instance without leaving or logging out.

tasks.name: Kree'arra Veteran
tasks.description: Kree'arra Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra 100 times.

tasks.name: Leviathan Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Leviathan Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan in under 1 minute and 50 seconds, without being on a slayer task.

tasks.name: Leviathan Adept
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Leviathan Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan once after completion of Desert Treasure II.

tasks.name: High Hitter
tasks.prereqs: Perilous Moons quest; 48 Slayer; 20 Hunter; 20 Fishing; 20 Runecrafting; 10 Construction
tasks.description:
High Hitter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon before they start their second special attack.
This combat achievement does not count special attacks that are happening as you enter the room, so players struggling with this task may wish to enter shortly after a special starts, to give them more time.

tasks.name: Nex Veteran
tasks.description: Nex Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex once.

tasks.name: Nex Survivors
tasks.description: Nex Survivors is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex without having anyone die during the fight.

tasks.name: Versatile Drainer
tasks.prereqs: Secrets of the North quest; 69 Agility; 64 Thieving; 56 Hunter
tasks.description: Versatile Drainer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to drain the Phantom Muspah's prayer with three different sources in one kill.

tasks.name: Phantom Muspah Veteran
tasks.prereqs: Secrets of the North quest; 69 Agility; 64 Thieving; 56 Hunter
tasks.description: Phantom Muspah Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah 25 times.

tasks.name: Phantom Muspah Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Secrets of the North quest; 69 Agility; 64 Thieving; 56 Hunter
tasks.description: Phantom Muspah Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah in less than 3 minutes without a Slayer task.

tasks.name: Can't Escape
tasks.prereqs: Secrets of the North quest; 69 Agility; 64 Thieving; 56 Hunter
tasks.description:
Can't Escape is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah without running.
This achievement fails as soon as the player either leaves the starting tile with Run on, or turns Run on at any point during the fight. Only walking is permissible.

tasks.name: Phosani's Veteran
tasks.description: Phosani's Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare once.

tasks.name: No time to pray
tasks.description: No time to pray is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without losing any prayer points.

tasks.name: Scorpia Veteran
tasks.description: Scorpia Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia 25 times.

tasks.name: Up for the Challenge
tasks.description: Up for the Challenge is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo, or Awakened Altars without equipping a demonbane weapon.

tasks.name: Demon Evasion
tasks.description: Demon Evasion is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo without taking any damage.

tasks.name: Perfect Hueycoatl
tasks.description: Perfect Hueycoatl is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl perfectly 5 times without leaving. Only the player seeking the achievement must get a perfect kill; other players in the fight do not need to.

tasks.name: Hueycoatl Veteran
tasks.description: Hueycoatl Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl 25 times.

tasks.name: Hueycoatl Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Hueycoatl Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl in 2:30.

tasks.name: Mimic Veteran
tasks.description:
Mimic Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Mimic once.
In order to be eligible to obtain a Mimic, players must first speak to the strange casket upstairs in Watson's house in Hosidius to enable the chance of a reward casket turning into the Mimic. An elite reward casket has a 1/35 chance of being a mimic, while master reward caskets have a 1/15 chance. There is a one-time guaranteed Mimic encounter on either the 11th master or 26th elite casket, whichever is first.

tasks.name: Sleep Tight
tasks.description: Sleep Tight is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Nightmare solo.

tasks.name: Nightmare Veteran
tasks.description: Nightmare Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat The Nightmare 25 times. Phosani's Nightmare kills will also count towards this achievement.

tasks.name: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Trialist elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare, solo, in under 23 minutes.

tasks.name: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare in a team of 5 players in under 5 minutes.

tasks.name: Explosion!
tasks.description: Explosion! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill two Husks at the same time.

tasks.name: Theatre of Blood Veteran
tasks.description:
Theatre of Blood Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood 25 times. Hard Mode Theatre of Blood completions will also count towards this achievement.
Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode does not count towards the completion of this achievement.

tasks.name: They Won't Expect This
tasks.description: They Won't Expect This is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode, enter the Pestilent Bloat room from the opposite side.

tasks.name: Pass It On
tasks.description:
Pass It On is an elite combat achievement which requires the player in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode, to successfully pass on the green ball to a team mate.
The green ball is a special attack launched by Verzik Vitur in her third phase.

tasks.name: Nylocas, On the Rocks
tasks.description: Nylocas, On the Rocks is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to freeze any 4 nylocas with a single Ice Barrage spell during a Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode raid. As the achievement is completed immediately after freezing 4 nylocas, the raid does not need to be completed.

tasks.name: No-Pillar
tasks.description: No-Pillar is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to survive Verzik Vitur's pillar phase in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without losing a single pillar.

tasks.name: Just To Be Safe
tasks.description:
Just To Be Safe is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sotetseg in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode after having split the big ball with your entire team. This must be done with a group size of at least 2.
The big ball refers to the special attack by Sotetseg where it launches a big red ball that cannot be protected against. When multiple players stand on the same tile, the damage inflicted from the ball is split between the players. This attack is used after Sotetseg launches at least ten...

tasks.name: Don't Look at Me!
tasks.description: Don't Look at Me! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Xarpus in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without him reflecting any damage to anyone.

tasks.name: Chally Time
tasks.description: Chally Time is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Pestilent Bloat in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode by using a dragon halberd or crystal halberd special attack as your final attack.

tasks.name: Attack, Step, Wait
tasks.description: Attack, Step, Wait is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to survive Verzik Vitur's second phase in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without anyone getting bounced by Verzik.

tasks.name: Appropriate Tools
tasks.description:
Appropriate Tools is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Pestilent Bloat in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode with everyone having a salve amulet equipped.
This achievement can be completed with any version of the salve amulet.

tasks.name: Anticoagulants
tasks.description: Anticoagulants is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Maiden of Sugadinti in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without letting a blood spawn live for more than 10 seconds.

tasks.name: Thermonuclear Veteran
tasks.description: Thermonuclear Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil 20 times.

tasks.name: Spec'd Out
tasks.description: Spec'd Out is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil using only special attacks.

tasks.name: Hazard Prevention
tasks.description: Hazard Prevention is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil without it hitting anyone.

tasks.name: Tomb Explorer
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Tomb Explorer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid once, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Perfect Het
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Perfect Het is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Het challenge room without taking any damage from the light beam or orbs, and destroying Het's Seal in one cycle, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Perfect Crondis
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Perfect Crondis is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Crondis challenge room without letting a crocodile get to the tree, without anyone losing water from their container and in under one minute, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Perfect Apmeken
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Perfect Apmeken is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Apmeken challenge room in a group of two or more without allowing any dangers to trigger, standing in venom, or being hit by a volatile baboon, while completing the room within three minutes, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: No skipping allowed
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: No skipping allowed is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba while only destroying uncracked boulders, without dying, and having the Boulderdash invocation active, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: I'm in a rush
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: I'm in a rush is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba after destroying four or fewer rolling boulders in total without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Helpful spirit who?
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Helpful spirit who? is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 150 or above without relying on the Helpful Spirit for supplies.  The raid must be completed deathless by the entire party and will fail if any players in the raid use supplies from the Helpful Spirit.

tasks.name: Hardcore Tombs
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Hardcore Tombs is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid solo without dying, at level 150 or above. The Hardcore Run invocation does not need to be active in order to complete the achievement.

tasks.name: Hardcore Raiders
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Hardcore Raiders is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid in a group of two or more without anyone dying, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Dropped the ball
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Dropped the ball is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Akkha without dropping any materialising orbs and without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Down Do Specs
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Down Do Specs is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Wardens after staggering the boss twice during phase 2 without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

tasks.name: Novice Tomb Raider
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Novice Tomb Raider is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at any level 50 times.

tasks.name: Expert Tomb Explorer
tasks.prereqs: Beneath Cursed Sands quest; 62 Agility; 55 Crafting; 55 Firemaking
tasks.description: Expert Tomb Explorer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid once, at level 300 or above.

tasks.name: Unending Torment
tasks.prereqs: While Guthix Sleeps quest; 180 Quest Points; 72 Thieving; 67 Magic; 66 Agility; 65 Farming; 65 Herblore; 62 Hunter; A Combined Strength and Attack Level of 130 (or 99 in one)
tasks.description:
Unending Torment is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Tormented Demon. 
This achievement will only count as completed for Tormented Demons killed after the completion of While Guthix Sleeps. The two Tormented Demons killed during the quest while player's stats are temporarily increased due to touching the Stone of Jas do not count towards task completion.

tasks.name: Two Times the Torment
tasks.prereqs: While Guthix Sleeps quest; 180 Quest Points; 72 Thieving; 67 Magic; 66 Agility; 65 Farming; 65 Herblore; 62 Hunter; A Combined Strength and Attack Level of 130 (or 99 in one)
tasks.description: Two Times the Torment is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill two Tormented Demons within two seconds.

tasks.name: Through Fire and Flames
tasks.prereqs: While Guthix Sleeps quest; 180 Quest Points; 72 Thieving; 67 Magic; 66 Agility; 65 Farming; 65 Herblore; 62 Hunter; A Combined Strength and Attack Level of 130 (or 99 in one)
tasks.description: Through Fire and Flames is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Tormented Demon whilst their fire shield is inactive, which is the duration they throw out the fireballs and stun.

tasks.name: Rapid Reload
tasks.prereqs: While Guthix Sleeps quest; 180 Quest Points; 72 Thieving; 67 Magic; 66 Agility; 65 Farming; 65 Herblore; 62 Hunter; A Combined Strength and Attack Level of 130 (or 99 in one)
tasks.description: Rapid Reload is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to hit three tormented demons within three seconds using a ballista or crossbow.

tasks.name: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's first challenge in less than 45 seconds.

tasks.name: The II Jad Challenge
tasks.description: The II Jad Challenge is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's second challenge.

tasks.name: Facing Jad Head-on III
tasks.description: Facing Jad Head-on III is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's second challenge with only melee.

tasks.name: Half-Way There
tasks.description: Half-Way There is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Jal-Zek within the Inferno. Jal-Zek is first encountered on wave 35 of the Inferno.

tasks.name: Fight Caves Veteran
tasks.description: Fight Caves Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves once.

tasks.name: Facing Jad Head-on
tasks.description: Facing Jad Head-on is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves with only melee weapons equipped. Players are allowed to log out and back into the same world and still be eligible for the combat achievement, but hopping worlds is not allowed.

tasks.name: A Near Miss!
tasks.description: A Near Miss! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves after surviving a hit from TzTok-Jad without praying.

tasks.name: Vardorvis Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Vardorvis Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis in less than 1 minute and 15 seconds without a slayer task.

tasks.name: Vardorvis Adept
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Vardorvis Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis once after completion of the Desert Treasure II quest.

tasks.name: Venenatis Veteran
tasks.description: Venenatis Veteran is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill Venenatis 20 times. Both Venenatis and her singles-plus variant Spindel kills count towards this task.

tasks.name: Vet'eran
tasks.description: Vet'eran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vet'ion 20 times. Both Vet'ion and his singles-plus variant Calvar'ion kills count towards this task.

tasks.name: Zombie Destroyer
tasks.prereqs: Dragon Slayer 2 quest; 200 Quest Points; 75 Magic; 70 Smithing; 68 Mining; 62 Crafting; 60 Agility; 60 Thieving; 50 Construction; 50 Hitpoints
tasks.description: Zombie Destroyer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath's zombified spawn without using crumble undead.

tasks.name: Vorkath Veteran
tasks.prereqs: Dragon Slayer 2 quest; 200 Quest Points; 75 Magic; 70 Smithing; 68 Mining; 62 Crafting; 60 Agility; 60 Thieving; 50 Construction; 50 Hitpoints
tasks.description: Vorkath Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath 50 times.

tasks.name: Stick 'em With the Pointy End
tasks.prereqs: Dragon Slayer 2 quest; 200 Quest Points; 75 Magic; 70 Smithing; 68 Mining; 62 Crafting; 60 Agility; 60 Thieving; 50 Construction; 50 Hitpoints
tasks.description: Stick 'em With the Pointy End is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath using melee weapons only.

tasks.name: Whisperer Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Whisperer Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer in under 3 minutes without being on a slayer task.

tasks.name: Whisperer Adept
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Whisperer Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer once after completion of the Desert Treasure II quest.

tasks.name: Tentacular
tasks.prereqs: Desert Treasure 2 quest; 75 Firemaking; 75 Magic; 70 Thieving; 62 Herblore; 60 Runecraft; 60 Construction
tasks.description: Tentacular is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer while on the Arceuus spellbook. You can complete this combat achievement with the Whisperer's awakened variant.

tasks.name: Yama Speed-Trialist
tasks.prereqs: A Kingdom Divided quest; 54 Agility; 52 Thieving; 52 Woodcutting; 50 Herblore; 42 Mining; 38 Crafting; 35 Magic
tasks.description: Yama Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama in an average time of under 3:38 over the player's most recent four kills.

tasks.name: Yama Adept
tasks.prereqs: A Kingdom Divided quest; 54 Agility; 52 Thieving; 52 Woodcutting; 50 Herblore; 42 Mining; 38 Crafting; 35 Magic
tasks.description: Yama Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama once.

tasks.name: Back so soon?
tasks.prereqs: A Kingdom Divided quest; 54 Agility; 52 Thieving; 52 Woodcutting; 50 Herblore; 42 Mining; 38 Crafting; 35 Magic
tasks.description: Back so soon? is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without the Judge of Yama being attacked with the wrong style, and without taking more than one instance of damage each time you are exiled from the arena.

tasks.name: Zalcano Veteran
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Zalcano Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano 25 times.

tasks.name: The Spurned Hero
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description:
The Spurned Hero is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano as the player who has dealt the most damage to her.
The achievement checks for the amount of mining damage dealt to Zalcano after breaking her stone armour, rather than checking whether the player is the MVP for that kill (i.e. the one who receives the infernal ashes upon defeating her).

tasks.name: Team Player
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Team Player is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive imbued tephra from a golem.

tasks.name: Perfect Zalcano
tasks.prereqs: Song of the Elves quest; 70 Agility; 70 Construction; 70 Farming; 70 Herblore; 70 Hunter; 70 Mining; 70 Smithing; 70 Woodcutting
tasks.description: Perfect Zalcano is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano 5 times in a row without leaving or getting hit by the following: Falling rocks, rock explosions, Zalcano powering up, or standing in a red symbol.

tasks.name: Zulrah Veteran
tasks.description: Zulrah Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah 75 times.

tasks.name: Zulrah Speed-Trialist
tasks.description: Zulrah Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah in less than 1 minute 20 seconds, without a slayer task.

tasks.name: Snake. Snake!? Snaaaaaake!
tasks.description: Snake. Snake!? Snaaaaaake! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill 3 snakelings simultaneously while fighting Zulrah.

tasks.name: Snake Rebound
tasks.description: Snake Rebound is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah by using the Vengeance spell as the finishing blow.

tasks.name: Don't Flame Me
tasks.description: Don't Flame Me is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its flame wall attack.

tasks.name: The Flame Skipper
tasks.description:
The Flame Skipper is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without letting it spawn a flame wall attack.
This achievement will only count as completed if the Hydra does not reach the middle and stop moving before changing phases.

tasks.name: Unrequired Antipoisons
tasks.description: Unrequired Antipoisons is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its acid pool attack.

tasks.name: Mixing Correctly
tasks.description: Mixing Correctly is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without empowering it.

tasks.name: Alcleanical Hydra
tasks.description: Alcleanical Hydra is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without taking any damage.

tasks.name: Alchemical Speed-Chaser
tasks.description: Alchemical Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra in under 1 minute and 45 seconds.

tasks.name: Lightning Lure
tasks.description: Lightning Lure is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its lightning attack.

tasks.name: Working Overtime
tasks.description: Working Overtime is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 15 times without leaving the room.

tasks.name: Alchemical Master
tasks.description: Alchemical Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 150 times.

tasks.name: Araxxor Speed-Chaser
tasks.description: Araxxor Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 5 times in 10:00.

tasks.name: Perfect Araxxor
tasks.description: Perfect Araxxor is a master combat achievement requiring the player to perfectly kill Araxxor.

tasks.name: Arachnid Lover
tasks.description: Arachnid Lover is a master combat achievement requiring the player to kill Araxxor 10 times without leaving his lair.

tasks.name: Araxyte Betrayal
tasks.description: Araxyte Betrayal is a master combat achievement which requires the player to have an araxyte kill three other araxytes.

tasks.name: Let it seep in
